[DataRow(2L, "Bob")]
public void GetUserName_ReturnsCorrectName(int id, string expectedName)

// Fix — either change literals to int:
[DataRow(1, "Alice")]
[DataRow(2, "Bob")]

// Or change parameter to long:
public void GetUserName_ReturnsCorrectName(long id, string expectedName)
```

**4. Timeout behavior** — `[Timeout(3000)]` on line 32 will still work, but behavior is now unified across .NET Core and Framework. Verify it behaves as expected after upgrading.

